title: Add default cache timeout per provider to available models table
---
Add a default caching timeout column/field for each provider in the available models table. This is the prompt cache TTL for that provider's API.

Default is usually ~5 minutes for most providers (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.), but some upcoming models may have significantly longer cache windows (e.g. gpt-5.6 reportedly will have 30-minute cache timeouts once released).

This data is needed for:
- Intelligent subagent_result blocking (B724): block up to cache timeout minus safety margin
- Cache-aware session management: know when a context switch/cache miss is likely
- Cost estimation: cached vs uncached token pricing depends on cache hit probability which depends on TTL

Should be stored per-provider (not per-model) since cache behavior is typically uniform within a provider, with model-specific overrides where known.